  "title": "Plant Manager $5K - $7K + VB (Industry: Waste Treatment / WWTP / Industrial Operations)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Leadership role in established waste treatment operations</li><li>Stable full-time position with growth opportunities</li><li>Exposure to process improvement & plant optimisation</li></ul><p><strong>Role Summary</strong></p><p>Responsible for end-to-end operations of a waste treatment facility, ensuring <strong>safe and efficient plant performance</strong>. You will lead operations, manpower, and continuous improvement initiatives while maintaining high EHS and operational standards.</p><p><strong>Key Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure <strong>full compliance with EHS and regulatory requirements</strong></li><li>Manage daily plant operations to meet <strong>throughput and uptime targets</strong></li><li>Coordinate maintenance to minimise unplanned downtime</li><li>Lead, schedule, and develop operations teams (including foreign workers)</li><li>Oversee plant housekeeping, 5S standards, and inventory control</li><li>Prepare operational, safety, and KPI reports</li><li>Drive process improvements to reduce <strong>chemical, energy, and waste costs</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Environmental, Chemical Engineering, or related field</li><li><strong>7 - 10 years</strong> in Waste Treatment or Industrial Plant Operations</li><li>Minimum <strong>3 years in Managerial role</strong></li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>physical, chemical, and biological treatment systems</strong></li><li>Proven leadership, safety mindset, and attention to detail</li></ul><p>📧 <strong>Apply Now: </strong>jeffrey@oaktree.com.sg<br />👤 <strong>Contact: </strong>Jeffrey Chua Kay Hwee<br />EA License No: 06C4642 | EA Reg No: R1110624</p>",
